With The FEDERAL ENERGY REGULATORY COMMISSION Version 1.0.0 Orange and Rockland Utilities, Inc. Page 1 Market Based Rates Tariff, FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 4 Version 1.0.0 TABLE OF CONTENTS 1.0 DEFINITIONS 2.0 SERVICES AND LIMITATIONS 2.1 Availability 2.2 Applicability 2.3 Compliance with FERC Regulations 2.4 Seller Category 2.4 Limitations and Exemptions 2.5 Rates 2.6 Other Terms and Conditions 3.0 CREDITWORTHINESS 3.1 Financial Information 3.2 Payment Guarantees 4.0 SERVICE AGREEMENT 4.1 Service Agreement 4.2 Agreement 4.3 Transaction Memoranda 4.4 Cancellation 5.0 NATURE AND PRIORITY OF SERVICE 5.1 Transactions Voluntary 5.2 Priority 5.3 Bankruptcy 6.0 DELIVERY POINT 6.1 Delivery Point 6.2 Metering 7.0 SCHEDULING AND OPERATING PROCEDURES 7.1 Procedures 8.0 CHARGES 8.1 Advance Determination 8.2 Separate Charges 9.0 GENERAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS 9.1 Billings and Payments 9.1.1 Monthly Billings 9.1.2 Payment 9.1.3 Due Date 9.1.4 Billing Disputes 9.1.5 Billing Adjustments 9.1.6 Interest 9.1.7 Default 9.2 Liability and Indemnification 9.3 Force Majeure 9.4 Records 9.5 Successors and Assigns 9.6 Notices 9.7 Regulation 9.8 Term of Tariff 9.9 After Termination or Cancellation 9.10 Governing Law and Venue 9.11 Confidentiality FORM OF SERVICE AGREEMENT 1.0 DEFINITIONS The following words or terms used on this Tariff shall have the meanings indicated below: 1.1 Capacity: Electric capacity from various sources made available by Orange and Rockland to be sold pursuant to this Tariff. 1.2 Customer: Any entity (including, but not limited to any investor owned corporation, municipal electric system, rural electric cooperative or an association of such or similar entities authorized by state law to provide public utility services) (i) that is engaged in the sale of electricity for resale or at retail to ultimate customers and (ii) that executes or proposes to execute a Service Agreement. Ultimate consumers of electric utility service (i.e., retail customers) are not eligible as a Customer. 1.3 Energy: Electric energy from various sources made available by Orange and Rockland to be sold pursuant to this Tariff. 1.4 Federal Power Act ("FPA"): The Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. §792 et seq., as it is now or may be amended in the future, or any successor thereto. 1.5 FERC: The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, or its successor having regulatory jurisdiction over this Tariff. 1.6 MWH: Megawatthour or Megawatthours. 1.7 PSC: New York State Public Service Commission. 1.8 NYISO: New York Independent System Operator. 1.9 NYSRC: New York State Reliability Council. 1.10 Orange and Rockland: Orange and Rockland Utilities, Inc. 1.11 Orange and Rockland's Open Access Tariff: Orange and Rockland's Open Access Transmission Tariff filed on July 9, 1996 in FERC Docket No. OA96-210-000, or any successor thereto. 1.12 Parties: The parties to a Service Agreement executed pursuant to this Tariff. 1.13 Service Agreement: An agreement between Orange and Rockland and Customer for service under this Tariff. 1.14 System Constraints: Conditions on the generation, transmission or distribution facilities of Orange and Rockland or any transmitting utility which, consistent with good utility practice, require the interruption of a Transaction made pursuant to this Tariff in order to maintain system integrity and to maintain safety and reliability. 1.15 Tariff: This Orange and Rockland Electric Tariff as it is now or as it may be amended of supplemented from time to time in accordance with the terms hereof. 1.16 Transaction: A separately-arranged reservation or sale of Capacity and/or Energy to a Customer under this Tariff. 2.0 SERVICES AND LIMITATIONS 2.1 Availability: Orange and Rockland (Seller) may sell electric energy and capacity under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale, except as prohibited in paragraph 1A.4. Seller may also sell ancillary services under this Rate Schedule into the markets administered by ISO New England (ISO-NE), PJM Interconnection, LLC (PJM), New York Independent System Operator (NYISO), and on a bilateral basis within the control areas that they administer. The ancillary services that Seller may make available under this Rate Schedule include: a) New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the NYISO. b) New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO-NE. c) PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 2.2 Applicability: This Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity or ancillary services by Orange and Rockland that are not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Orange and Rockland or of ISO-NE, PJM, or the NYISO. 2.3 Compliance with FERC Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Sellers market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Sellers market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Sellers market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 2.4 Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. § 35.36(a), in the following region: Northeast. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. § 35.36(a), in the following regions: Central, Southeast, Northwest, Southwest Power Pool, Southwest, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a). 2.4 Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: The following limitations and exemptions or waivers to the FERCs regulations apply to sales under this tariff: a) With respect to energy management contracts that Orange and Rockland enters, Orange and Rockland will comply with all mitigation requirements that may apply to the generator involved. 2.5 Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Orange and Rockland. 2.6 Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Orange and Rockland. 3.0 CREDITWORTHINESS 3.1 Financial Information: Prior to the execution or during the term of a Service Agreement, Orange and Rockland may require Customer to provide financial information necessary to establish Customer's creditworthiness, including the following information: (a) current financial statements, annual reports, and other publicly available reports and filings; (b) a bank reference and trade references; and (c) verification of Customer's solvency. 3.2 Payment Guarantees: In lieu of providing financial information pursuant to Section 2.1, Customer may provide security that Orange and Rockland reasonably deems necessary to establish Customer's creditworthiness. 4.0 SERVICE AGREEMENT 4.1 Service Agreement: Each Customer shall execute a Service Agreement as a condition precedent to Orange and Rockland's provision of service hereunder, which agreement shall be filed with the FERC by Orange and Rockland. 4.2 Agreement: By signing a Service Agreement, the Customer agrees to take and pay for, and Orange and Rockland agrees to supply, such Energy and/or Capacity as is mutually agreed upon, subject to the terms and conditions of this Tariff, and such other terms and conditions agreed upon by Orange and Rockland and the Customer. In addition, both Orange and Rockland and customer agree to comply with all applicable requirements established by Orange and Rockland or other entity having authority with respect to regional power transactions. The terms of this Tariff shall apply to all sales hereunder, except insofar as they are expressly modified by a Service Agreement. 4.3 Transaction Memoranda: The terms and conditions agreed upon for each Transaction shall be stated on a Transaction Memorandum that shall be signed by Orange and Rockland and Customer and made an exhibit to the Service Agreement. 4.4 Cancellation: Orange and Rockland reserves the right to cancel the Service Agreement between Orange and Rockland and Customer and/or to terminate Transactions under the Service Agreement consistent with the provisions of FERC's regulations governing notices of cancellation or termination; provided that such cancellation or termination shall not be effective prior to the completion of any on-going Transaction. 5.0 NATURE AND PRIORITY OF SERVICE 5.1 Transactions Voluntary: Upon execution of a Service Agreement by Customer, Orange and Rockland may sell and Customer may purchase, from time to time, Capacity and/or Energy upon such terms and conditions and in such quantities as Orange and Rockland and Customer agree. Neither Orange and Rockland nor Customer shall be obligated to enter into any particular Transaction, except as they agree. 5.2 Priority: The priority and nature of service shall be negotiated between Orange and Rockland and Customer and specified in the Transaction Memorandum. 5.3 Bankruptcy and Insolvency: Orange and Rockland shall not be required to execute a Service Agreement or a Transaction Memorandum or to continue a Transaction if (a) Customer files a voluntary petition or has an involuntary petition filed against it, for bankruptcy under the United States Bankruptcy Code, 11 U.S.C. §§101 et seq., or similar state insolvency laws: (b) Customer otherwise becomes insolvent and regularly fails to meet its payment obligations when due; or (c) upon review of the financial data in Section 2.1, Orange and Rockland may continue to provide Capacity and Energy if Customer prepays for such service or furnishes reasonable security to assure payment of Customer's liabilities under its Service Agreement. 6.0 DELIVERY POINT 6.1 Delivery Point: All deliveries of energy hereunder will be made at delivery point(s) designated by the mutual agreement of Orange and Rockland and Customer; provided that such delivery point(s) shall be located outside of Orange and Rockland's franchised service territory or at a point of interconnection of the transmission facilities of Orange and Rockland and those of another transmitting utility. 6.2 Metering: Deliveries of Capacity and Energy shall be metered at the point of delivery. The metering equipment shall be maintained in accordance with good utility practice. 7.0 SCHEDULING AND OPERATING PROCEDURES 7.1 Procedures: Throughout the term of this Tariff, Orange and Rockland shall maintain in effect scheduling and operating procedures governing the provision of service hereunder. Such procedures shall specify content, deadlines and contact points for communications which Orange and Rockland may require for scheduling, operating, reporting and accounting purposes, and shall be consistent with the requirements established by the NYISO or NYSRC or any other entity having authority with respect to regional power transactions. 8.0 CHARGES 8.1 Advance Determination: Prior to the commencement of a Transaction, Orange and Rockland and Customer shall agree in writing upon starting date and time, duration, quantity, rates, charges, and other terms of the Transaction. These terms shall be set forth on a Transaction Memorandum. 8.2 Separate Charges: Orange and Rockland and Customer shall agree to prices for Energy and/or Capacity separate from any charges for transmission services and ancillary services, and the Transaction Memorandum shall state such separate prices for Energy and/or Capacity. 9.0 GENERAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS 9.1 Billings and Payments 9.1.1 Monthly Billing: As soon as practicable after the end of the calendar month during which a Transaction takes place, Orange and Rockland shall render to customer a bill for charges accruing during the month. The bill shall incorporate such information as may be reasonably necessary to determine the payments due. If actual meter readings are not available at the time a bill is rendered, the bill may be based upon estimated data; provided that reconciled charges, based upon actual meter readings, shall be stated on the next monthly bill. 9.1.2 Payment: Customer shall pay all bills rendered under this Tariff no later than the Due Date (as defined in Section 8.1.3). Customer shall make payment in immediately available funds by wire transfer. Any amount remaining unpaid after the Due Date will be deemed delinquent and will accrue interest at the annual rate of two percent (2%) over the interest rate on prime commercial loans then in effect at the main office of Citibank N.A., located in New York, New York, calculated from the Due Date to the date the amount is paid in full. 9.1.3 Due Date: Except as otherwise provided in this section, the Due Date for a bill will be the later of (i) ten (10) days after receipt of the bill, or (ii) the first banking day common to Orange and Rockland and Customer following the nineteenth day of the month in which the bill was rendered. If the Due Date should fall on a Saturday, Sunday, or holiday, the Due Date will be the next Orange and Rockland business day after such weekend or holiday. 9.1.4 Billing Disputes: Customer may in good faith challenge the correctness of any bill rendered under this Tariff, provided that such challenge is brought within twelve (12) months after the date the bill was rendered. Any billing challenge shall be in writing and shall state the specific basis for the challenge. In the event that Customer challenges any portion of a bill, Customer shall, despite the challenge, pay both the disputed and undisputed portions of the bill on or before the Due Date. 9.1.5 Billing Adjustments: Orange and Rockland may adjust any bill rendered under this Tariff, provided that such adjustment is made within twelve (12) months after the date the bill was rendered. Any billing adjustment shall be in writing and shall state the specific basis for the adjustment. A billing adjustment will constitute a new bill for all purposes of this Section 8.1. 9.1.6 Interest: Refunds and additional charges that are due as a result of a billing adjustment or billing challenge will include interest calculated at the rate specified in Section 8.1.2. In the case of an additional charge, interest will be calculated from the Due Date of the bill to which the adjustment or challenge relates to the date the additional charge is paid to Orange and Rockland. In the case of a refund, interest will be calculated from the date the amount being refunded was received by Orange and Rockland to the date the refund is made. 9.1.7 Default: In the event that Customer fails to make full payment of a bill rendered under this Tariff on or before the Due Date and such default continues for thirty (30) days after the Due Date, Orange and Rockland shall have the right to suspend or terminate any existing Transactions and to file with the FERC a notice of cancellation of the Service Agreement pursuant to 18 CFR Section 35.15. 9.2 Liability and Indemnification: Neither Orange and Rockland nor Customer shall be responsible to each other in tort (including negligence and strict liability), contract or otherwise for any loss, cost, or damage of any kind, which may result from performance or non-performance of obligations under this Tariff, except for losses, costs, or damages resulting from gross negligence or willful misconduct; provided in any event that neither Orange and Rockland nor Customer shall be liable for incidental, consequential, punitive, special, and indirect damages, which may result from performance or non-performance of obligations under this Tariff. Customer expressly agrees to indemnify, hold harmless and defend Orange and Rockland against all claims, liability, costs, attorneys' fees, recoveries, court costs, and all other obligations to third parties, or expense for loss, damage, injury, or death to persons or property in any manner directly or indirectly connected with or growing out of, the performance or actions of Orange and Rockland pursuant to this Tariff on behalf of Customer, except insofar as such liabilities arise because of gross negligence or willful misconduct by Orange and Rockland. Nothing herein shall create, or be interpreted as creating, any standard of care with reference to, or any duty or liability to any person not a Customer hereunder. 9.3 Force Majeure: in the event that either Orange and Rockland or Customer is delayed in or prevented from performing or carrying out its obligations under this Tariff or a Service Agreement, in whole or in part, by reason of Force Majeure, such Party shall not be liable to the other Party for or on account of any loss, damage, injury or expense resulting from or arising out of such delay or prevention. "Force Majeure" means any cause beyond the reasonable control of the Party claiming Force Majeure, including, without limitation as to the nature or kind of events, sabotage, strikes, lockouts or other labor disputes, riots, disorders or civil disturbances, vandalism, acts of God, acts of public enemy, droughts, epidemics, earthquakes, floods, explosions, fires, storms, snow, hail, ice, lightning, wind, landslides, washouts, embargoes, acts of military authorities, actions or inactions of local, state or federal legislative, judicial or regulatory agencies or other proper authorities, arrests, restraints, system outages, System Constraints, inability to obtain or failure of equipment, and transportation delays. The Party encountering such delay or prevention shall notify the other as soon as reasonably possible of the delay or prevention and shall use due diligence to remove promptly the cause or causes thereof. In order to be relieved of obligations pursuant to this Section 8.3, neither Orange and Rockland or Customer shall be required to settle any strike, walkout, lockout or other labor dispute on terms which, in the sole judgment of the party involved in the dispute, are contrary to its interest. Force Majeure shall not excuse the failure to pay bills on their Due Dates. 9.4 Records: Orange and Rockland and Customer shall each keep complete and accurate records of all Transactions conducted pursuant to this Tariff. Orange and Rockland and Customer shall maintain such records for a period of at least two years. Orange and Rockland and Customer shall make such records available for inspection, copying and audit by Orange and Rockland or Customer at reasonable times and places upon request. 9.5 Successors and Assigns: Any Service Agreement shall be binding upon the Parties thereto, their successors and assigns, on and after the effective date of such Service Agreement. Such Service Agreement may not be assigned by Customer, in whole or in part, to any third party without the prior written consent of Orange and Rockland, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld. 9.6 Notices: All notices provided pursuant to this Tariff or any Service Agreement hereunder shall be in writing and addressed as set forth in the Service Agreement. 9.7 Regulation: The provision of service by Orange and Rockland under this Tariff and any Service Agreement is subject to the jurisdiction of the FERC. Nothing contained in this Tariff or any Service Agreement entered into hereunder shall be construed as affecting or limiting in any way the right of Orange and Rockland unilaterally to file with the FERC, or make application to the FERC for, changes to this Tariff; provided that such changes shall not amend the terms and conditions of any Transaction for which Orange and Rockland and Customer have executed a Transaction Memorandum. 9.8 Term of Tariff: This Tariff shall become effective when it has been accepted for filing by order of the FERC under the FPA, in which case the effective date of this Tariff shall be as specified in the said FERC order. However, if the FERC or any reviewing court, in such order or in any separate order, imposes any condition, limitation or qualification under any of the provisions of the FPA which, individually or in the aggregate, Orange and Rockland determines to be adverse to Orange and Rockland, then Orange and Rockland may, at its option, terminate this Tariff in light of such FERC or court action. Otherwise, this Tariff shall remain effective until terminated by Orange and Rockland and upon thirty (30) days notice and receipt of all regulatory approvals necessary for such termination. 9.9 After Termination or Cancellation: The applicable provisions of this Tariff and any Service Agreement entered into under this Tariff shall continue in effect after termination or cancellation thereof to the extent necessary to provide for final billing, billing adjustments and payments, and with respect to any Party's indemnification obligations hereunder. 9.10 Governing Law and Venue: The validity and meaning of this Tariff and any Service Agreement entered into hereunder shall be governed by the laws of the State of New York. All disputes arising out of the performance of this Agreement shall be settled in the State or Federal Courts located within the City of New York or before the FERC. 9.11 Confidentiality: Orange and Rockland and Customer shall treat as confidential all prices and terms and conditions of any proposed or actual Transaction hereunder ("Confidential Matter"). Confidential Matter shall be for the sole and exclusive use of Orange and Rockland and Customer, and, subject to the provisions set forth below, neither Orange and Rockland nor customer shall publish, disclose, or otherwise divulge the Confidential Matter to any person at any time without the prior written consent of the other unless the release of the Confidential Matter is pursuant to a requirement imposed by the FERC or any other governmental or judicial body of competent jurisdiction. When either Orange and Rockland or Customer receives from any other entity or person a request for Confidential Matter, not then in the public domain, it shall inform the other of such request as soon as reasonably practicable. Orange and Rockland and Customer shall reasonably cooperate with each other in the exercise of any applicable rights to oppose the disclosure of the Confidential Matter to the requester or to prevent the Confidential Matter from becoming part of the public domain. Confidential Matter need not be treated confidentially once it has passed into the public domain. FORM OF SERVICE AGREEMENT This Agreement is entered into this ______ day of ____________, 20__ by and between _______________________ ("Customer") and ORANGE AND ROCKLAND UTILITIES, INC. ("Orange and Rockland"). In consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements herein, Customer and Orange and Rockland (Orange and Rockland and the Customer are each sometimes referred to individually as a Party and collectively as the "Parties") hereby agree as follows: Article 1. Service. 1.1 Orange and Rockland agrees, during the term of this Agreement, to sell electric energy and/or capacity to Customer, and Customer agrees to pay for such sale, in accordance with Orange and Rockland's FERC Electric Tariff, First Revised Volume No. 4 for the Wholesale Sale of Electricity at Market-Based Rates ("Tariff") on file with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("FERC"). Transmission services and ancillary services, as necessary, shall be provided pursuant to the terms and conditions set forth in the Open Access Transmission Tariff of the New York Independent System Operator on file with the FERC. 1.2 The terms and conditions of such service shall be (1) governed by the Tariff, as it exists at the time of this Agreement or as subsequently amended, and (2) agreed upon by Customer and Orange and Rockland with respect to each separately-arranged reservation or sale of capacity and/or energy to a Customer under the Tariff ("Transaction"). The Tariff as it exists or as subsequently amended is incorporated in this Agreement by reference. The agreed upon terms and conditions for each Transaction shall be memorialized in a Transaction Memorandum, each of which shall become an exhibit to this Service Agreement. 1.3 In executing this Agreement, neither Orange and Rockland nor Customer commits to enter into any individual Transaction. Article 2. Effective Date and Term of Agreement 2.1 This Agreement shall become effective on the date first stated above. However, if the FERC or any reviewing court imposes any condition, limitation, or qualification under any of the provisions of the Federal Power Act ("FPA') which, individually or in the aggregate, Orange and Rockland determines to be adverse to Orange and Rockland, then Orange and Rockland, may, at its option, terminate or renegotiate the terms of this Agreement in light of such FERC or court action. Each Party will use its best efforts to take, or cause to be taken, all actions requisite to obtain the necessary approvals so that is Agreement shall become effective as provided herein at the earliest practicable date. 2.2 This Agreement shall remain effective until terminated by either Party on thirty (30) days written notice. ARTICLE 3. Notice 3.1 Any notice given pursuant to this Agreement or the Tariff shall be in writing and delivered to the following: If to Orange and Rockland: Orange and Rockland Utilities, Inc. One Blue Hill Plaza Pearl River, New York 10965 Attention: If to Customer: _________________________ _________________________ _________________________ _________________________ 3.2 The names and address for notice to either Party may be changed at any time by written notice to the other Party. IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Service Agreement to be executed by their respective authorized officials as of the date first above written.
